 The complex type hierarchy is used by most or all the hierarchical elements of act-like documents.</comment>

    Java class for hierarchy complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="hierarchy">
   <complexContent>
     <extension base="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}basehierarchy">
       <choice>
         <sequence>
           <element ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}intro" minOccurs="0"/>
           <choice maxOccurs="unbounded" minOccurs="0">
             <element ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}componentRef"/>
             <group ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}hierElements"/>
           </choice>
           <element ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}wrapUp" minOccurs="0"/>
         </sequence>
         <element ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}content"/>
       </choice>
       <attGroup ref="{http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0/CSD13}corereq"/>
     </extension>
   </complexContent>

      • getComponentRefOrClauseOrSection

        public List<Object> getComponentRefOrClauseOrSection()
        Gets the value of the componentRefOrClauseOrSection property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the componentRefOrClauseOrSection property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getComponentRefOrClauseOrSection().add(newItem);

      • getOtherAttributes

        public Map<QName,String> getOtherAttributes()
        Gets a map that contains attributes that aren't bound to any typed property on this class.

        the map is keyed by the name of the attribute and the value is the string value of the attribute. the map returned by this method is live, and you can add new attribute by updating the map directly. Because of this design, there's no setter.

        Returns:
        always non-null
